# Nexus CMS — Project Conventions

Monorepo (npm workspaces + Turbo) for a self-hosted CMS.

## Layout

- `apps/admin/` — Next.js 14 admin panel + REST API + MCP (port 3001, package `@nexus/admin`)
- `apps/blog/` — Next.js 14 public SSG blog (port 3000, package `@nexus/blog`)
- `apps/e2e/` — Playwright E2E suite (`@nexus/e2e`)
- `packages/db/`, `packages/mcp-server/` — shared packages
- `docker-compose.yml` — production stack (admin + blog + redis + nginx)

## Stack

- Node.js >= 20, npm 10+
- TypeScript (strict; avoid `any`)
- Next.js 14 App Router, React 18
- SQLite via `better-sqlite3` (admin); Redis via `ioredis`
- Validation: `zod`. UUIDs: `uuid` v4.
- Auth: JWT (`jsonwebtoken`) + bcrypt (cost 12)
- Sanitization: `sanitize-html` / DOMPurify
- Encryption (sensitive settings): AES-256-GCM via `lib/encryption.ts`

## Run scripts (root)

```bash
npm run dev         # turbo run dev
npm run build       # turbo run build
npm run lint        # turbo run lint (next lint)
npm run typecheck   # turbo run typecheck (tsc --noEmit)
npm test            # turbo run test (Vitest)
npm run test:e2e    # Playwright via apps/e2e
```

## Non-negotiables

- Never commit secrets. All config via `.env` (see `.env.example`).
- Any new behavior needs tests (see testing rule).
- API responses must never leak sensitive values (tokens, raw API keys); use `maskApiKey()`.
- WCAG 2.1 AA is required for all UI changes.
- Use design tokens (CSS custom properties), never hard-coded colors/sizes.
